### Mount Disk Image
# Uses: Ultimate64Client.MountDiskAsync(drive, file, type?, mode?)
# MCP Tool: ultimate_mount_disk
# Drives: 8 (primary), 9 (secondary), etc.
# Optional type: d64, g64, d71, g71, d81 (auto-detected from file extension if omitted)
# Optional mode: readwrite (default), readonly, unlinked

### Example 1: Basic mount (type auto-detected from extension)
POST http://localhost:8080/
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "ultimate_mount_disk",
    "arguments": {
      "drive": "8",
      "file": "/games/loderunner.d64"
    }
  }
}

###
### Example 2: Mount with explicit type and read-only mode
POST http://localhost:8080/
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 2,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "ultimate_mount_disk",
    "arguments": {
      "drive": "9",
      "file": "/disks/archive.d71",
      "type": "d71",
      "mode": "readonly"
    }
  }
}
